modules.description: This module implements an in-memory key-value store with support for time-stamped operations, partial content retrieval and updates, and directory-like listings. It works with keys represented as hierarchical paths and associates each value with metadata like modification time and size. It can be used to model virtual file systems in memory, such as for testing or building custom storage abstractions.

This module provides an in-memory key-value store that supports time-stamped operations, partial content retrieval and updates, and directory-like listings using hierarchical paths. It associates values with metadata such as modification time and size, enabling modeling of virtual file systems for testing or custom storage abstractions. Operations include reading, writing, listing, and deleting keys with precise control over content and metadata. Submodules extend functionality for specific use cases, such as time-based snapshots or layered storage views.
